EXPLANATION – Matter in bolded italics is new; matter between brackets [omitted material] is material to be omitted.
AN ACT relating to civil liability; providing immunity from civil
liability for certain acts and omissions of volunteer
security personnel of a religious organization under
certain circumstances; and providing other matters
properly relating thereto.
Legislative Counsel’s Digest:
1 Existing law provides that a volunteer of a charitable organization is immune
2 from liability for civil damages as a result of an act or omission concerning services
3 the volunteer performs for the charitable organization that are not supervisory in
4 nature and are not part of any duties or responsibilities the volunteer may have as
5 an officer, director or trustee of the charitable organization, unless the act is
6 intentional, willful, wanton or malicious. However, this provision of existing law
7 does not restrict the liability of a charitable organization for the acts or omissions of
8 a volunteer performing services on its behalf. (NRS 41.485) Existing law also
9 provides that, with certain exceptions, nonprofit corporations, associations and
10 organizations formed under the laws of this State are not immune from civil
11 liability for injury or damage arising out of negligent or wrongful acts under certain
12 circumstances. (NRS 41.480)
13 Section 1 of this bill provides that in addition to any other immunity from civil
14 liability provided by existing law, volunteer security personnel of a religious
15 organization who are providing safety, security or protection services for a religious
16 organization are immune from civil liability for injury or damage caused by their
