26 bill apply to a civil action that is filed on or after October 1, 2025.
THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF NEVADA, REPRESENTED IN
SENATE AND ASSEMBLY, DO ENACT AS FOLLOWS:
1 Section 1. Chapter 41 of NRS is hereby amended by adding
2 thereto a new section to read as follows:
3 1. In addition to any other immunity from civil liability
4 provided by law, volunteer security personnel of a religious
5 organization who are providing safety, security or protection
6 services for a religious organization are immune from civil
7 liability for injury or damage caused by their acts or omissions if:
8 (a) Such volunteer security personnel are acting within the
9 scope of their duties and responsibilities as volunteer security
10 personnel; and
11 (b) Such acts or omissions are not reckless, wanton or grossly
12 negligent.
13 2. In addition to any other immunity from civil liability
14 provided by law, a religious organization is immune from civil
15 liability for the acts or omissions of its volunteer security
16 personnel who are providing safety, security or protection services
17 on its behalf pursuant to subsection 1.
18 3. As used in this section:
19 (a) “Religious organization” means an organization for which
20 the primary purpose is the operation of a church, synagogue,
21 mosque, temple or other place of religious worship at which
22 religious services and activities are regularly conducted.
23 (b) “Volunteer security personnel” means persons who provide
24 safety, security or protection services for a religious organization:
25 (1) Without compensation, other than reimbursement for
26 actual and necessary expenses on behalf of or to benefit the
27 religious organization; and
28 (2) To protect persons who are attending a service, meeting,
29 class or other gathering held at, or sponsored by, the religious
30 organization or to secure and protect its property.
